        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>May 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1833</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I <sic>supose</sic> you wish to hear from us and how we<lb/> are and
                I have have this morning some time to spare<lb/> so I let you know we arrived here
                last <date>Monday</date> week at 7<lb/> oclock went in a carriage and after a long
                ride we came<lb/> to the most <persName>revt<add>?</add> Parsan Isaac B Seixas
                    Backey</persName> meeting<lb/> her sister with open arms kissing and hugging the children<lb/>
                <sic>comming</sic> round me Hollowery<add>?</add> and Cring<add>?</add>
                <persName>uncle Rehine</persName><lb/>
                <persName>seixas</persName> hardly any chance to say how do and in less than<lb/> 20
                minutes <persName>Mr &amp; Mrs <add>?</add> Philips</persName> came to say<lb/> how
                you do and invited us to dine with them on <date>Thursday</date><lb/> what we did
                promise to do next Day we were visited by almost<lb/> say one Hundred more or less
                and everyday some one came<lb/> to see us we have been returning visits since
                    <date>Sunday</date> but<lb/> have not been able to get <sic>throu</sic> Half and
                I expect by<lb/> about 3 weeks we may finish news I have more <add>?</add><lb/> I
                forget the governor hearing we were come to <placeName>new
                    <sic>york</sic></placeName><lb/> came yesterday to Town and ordered a general
                parade<lb/> on <date><sic>thursday</sic></date> that I might see what fine soldiers
                they have<lb/> got from <placeName>new <sic>york</sic></placeName> so you see I have
                said nonsense enough</p>
            <p>I Remain your friend <persName role="author">Zalma Rehine</persName></p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee> you will remember us to <persName>Mr &amp; Mrs
                    Allen</persName><lb/> I would name all but we can spare no time so you<lb/> will
                tell all we wish them Happy and desire to be<lb/> Remembered to them remember us to
                    <persName>Mrs Cousin</persName><lb/> tell her we hope she will be Quite
                recovered from<lb/> her <sic>indispossion</sic> when we return god bless you</p>
            <p><persName>Mr &amp; <sic>Mr</sic> Seixas</persName> send <sic>there</sic> love to you
                and wish you<lb/> would be here next <date><sic>Sabath</sic></date> 14 Days from
                this when<add>?</add><lb/> gersham<add>?</add>
                <add>Hebrew</add> and help to eat some of <sic>there</sic> cakes</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>the <addressee>revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p>
                <placeName>No 86 <sic>Valnut</sic> Street</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <pb n="5"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>May 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1833</date>.</p>
            <p>Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I <sic>supose</sic> you wish to hear from us<lb/> and how we are and
                I have <sic>have</sic> this morning<lb/> some time to spare so I let you know
                we<lb/> arrived here last <date>Monday</date> week at 7 oclock<lb/> went in a
                    <sic>carriadge</sic> and after a long ride<lb/> we came to the most
                    <persName>revd Parson Isaac B<lb/> Seixas Backey<add>?</add></persName> meeting
                her sister with<lb/> open arms Kissing and <sic>Huging</sic> the children<lb/>
                    comoning<add>?</add> round me Hollowing and <sic>Cring</sic>
                <persName>uncle<lb/> Rehina</persName>
                <persName>Seixas</persName> hardly any chance to say<lb/> how do and in less than 20
                minutes <persName>Mr &amp; Mrs<lb/> Naphtoly Philips</persName> come to say how you
                do and<lb/> invited us to dine with them on <date><sic>thursday</sic></date><lb/>
                which we did promise to do next Day we were<lb/> visited by almost say one Hundred
                more or<lb/> less and everyday some one came to see us<lb/> we have been returning
                visits some<lb/>
                <date>Sunday</date> but have not been able to get<lb/> through by Half and I expect
                by about 3<lb/> weeks we may finish news I have<lb/> none I forgot the governor
                Hearing we<lb/> were come to <placeName>New York</placeName> came yesterday<lb/> to
                Town and ordered a general parade on<lb/>
                <date>Thursday</date> that I might see what fine<lb/> soldiers they have got in
                    <placeName>New York</placeName> so<lb/> you can see I have said nonsense
                enough</p>
            <p>I Remain your friend <persName role="author">Zalma Rehina</persName></p>
            <p>Addressed to: <addressee>The revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>No 86 <sic>walnut</sic> Street</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
